{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4baec999-2836-459b-acdc-e7d5a9c2e528","content":"For a .NET Web API, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No auth (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD single-tenant |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD multi-tenant |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain example.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer auth without Azure AD, use `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually. You can also consider the newer **Minimal API** template (`dotnet new web`) for a lighter starting point.\n\nRun `dotnet new webapi --help` to see all available options for your installed SDK version.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a0a9d9d9-2855-4863-85da-cb7c6d9da0b0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to look at files.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about dotnet web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":353,"requestId":"7827:20D09C:7420E61:806CFF5:69F3FA00"},"id":"4890ca6b-d8d6-45b8-88fb-594b9a798747","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:39.823Z","parentId":"d137f05b-3403-4424-8135-987669c50036"}
